Though I'm not the biggest resolution maker because I don't love the pressure, I had one this year so I thought I might share it...

My resolution for 2023 is to be present with my emotions. To notice when they arise, decipher the ones that deserve my attention, and move away from the ones not based in reality. Some emotions deserve to stay and be dealt with, and some aren’t even real. See if you can start making that distinction. When I am in a spiral, I intend to do this work so that I don’t sit in a state of spinning longer than needed. 

Zerooooooo pressure, but any of you make any resolutions you want to share? I love to hear them.

Renovation/Interior Design Tips as we approach the home stretch of our renovation…

1. Make boards for each room/space so you can see how all of your selects will work together and keep track of what you’ve selected. 

2. When in doubt, search on @amazonhome.

3. Don’t be afraid to negotiate with sellers on @etsy 
4. Spend time sourcing vintage goods so the space really reflects you.

5. Don’t go super trendy, you will get sick of it super fast. Choose updated classics. 

6. Have radical acceptance that everything will take double as long as you think it will. 

7. Order all fixtures/plumbing/appliances, etc. in advance to keep to the timeline as much as possible. 

8. Spend $ on cabinetry. Quality cabinetry makes such a difference. 

9. Gather a few bids from different contractors and don’;t just go with the cheapest one. Choose the person who you think you will work the best with.

10. Utilize @Pinterest for Inspiration before shopping. You might realize you like a certain style you weren’t familiar with!

11. Figure out a color story you want to begin with to narrow your focus. There are lot of options in all design areas which can be overwhelming.

12. If you have design block, look for inspo. Outside of your screen. Nature, colors/textures in your environment, etc.

Becoming a mom was a windy road. So many questions, so little control.  But having these incredible women by my side (and so many more not pictured), leading with such grace and unrelenting dedication has made it so much easier for me. This community too. The support you have shown, the stories of encouragement, the blessings, all of it. We’ve really built something special here. 

Sonny’s 5 now and I’m starting to see more into his heart and I couldn’t be more delighted. He has his sh*t, don’t get me wrong, but he’s an empathetic soul with an eagerness to meet people and experience everything. These days are IT, you guys. Whether you’re a mom to a human, an animal, a plant, yourself, whatever, you’re responsible for nurturing and you deserve to be celebrated. Taking care of ourselves is tough, taking care of others is tougher if we don’t care of ourselves. ♥️♥️♥️ #happymothersday

-  taking in the outdoors in a present way
-  getting pampered and not feeling guilty about it
-  rocking in a rocking chair
-  drinking my coffee slowly
-  remembering to take my vitamins @perelelhealth

How are you finding a moment for yourself today?

Proof to show I take pics of the “fun” stuff or the outfit looks or the shareable moments, but usually not the dull, everyday, mundane stuff. This is me last night, on a rare night out- which made me feel alive! But if I’m being perfectly honest, I haven’t wanted to leave the house lately or motivate to engage in society. Omg, I sound crazy when I write it out!!! I don’t know whether it’s the LA June gloom, my semi-anti-social personality, the anticipation of being in my office soon, my period, or what. But I’ve been in a place. Yes, I’ve been able to be super productive- recorded a bunch, caught up on emails, paced around the house taking calls, paid bills, and tidied up ( over and over and over again ), but it has felt a little yuck. My breaks consist of reality tv and peanut butter and banana shakes. Repeatedly. Sounds nice, but not consistently. That’s ok though. Life is just phases. Next week, I’ll be sitting at my desk in our new office, ready to step out and create in a fresh environment, with team camaraderie. Is anyone else in a place and wanna talk about it? Safe space.

In light of this grayness, both mentally and physically (head to my stories if you want more context), Timmy and I are starting our WELLNESS challenge again tomorrow. We get into it on our podcast next week, but essentially, we each choose 5 things that make us feel more WELL and try to do them every day for an allotted period. My 5 things are:
1. Take my vitamins
2. Meditate
3. 5 minutes of journaling
4. Read for 30 minutes
5. Move my body in a meaningful way

Feel free to get creative with them! But take accountability when you can’t get something done. You’re only cheating yourself if you don’t ACTUALLY do the work. We then tally up how many we’ve done at the end of the day and keep a running tally. Do this with friends and get motivated by creating a fun jackpot. We are going to do two weeks this time. We wanted to go camping for a while & heard about the @ulumresorts near Moab, Utah. It looked breathtaking online so we decided it would be our first summer getaway destination with our friends! 

We flew from LAX -SLC. The flight was super easy ( under 2 hours ) but with snacks and an iPad, the kids did great. 

We stopped at Chungas, a local Mexican spot in SLC. Highly recommend, get the steak tacos! 

It took 4 hrs. to get from SLC to ULUM. Sonny got antsy with a million “are we there yets” but totally manageable.

We were greeted by the warmest faces and most refreshing sips of fresh hibiscus lemonade.

Our tent was gorgeous. 
I don’t like this word but it was ultimate glamping
Comfy beds
Wood burning furnace 
Toilets that flush 
A hot rain shower
Aesop toiletries 
Plush towels 
Soft robes 

First day we got there, we swam, ate, made s’mores and ate delicious seasonal food. The fact that there is a full functioning kitchen in the middle of this wild is just so awesome. 

We were EXHAUSTED and all slept til 8! 
 
The next day we took a drive to the Colorado river for some river rafting!
 
The water was 50 degrees but the boys jumped in and loved every second. Pro tip: bring towels. I felt like a shit mom. 
 
The property has three pools at different temperatures. A cold plunge, air temperature, and a hot tub. So amazing.
 
Since the three of us stayed in the tent together we listened to a sleep story on Calm and were all out in 10 min. There was a pullout couch for Sonny. He stayed in it 2 out of the 3 nights. 
 
The next day, we hiked to the top of the Looking Glass Rock. I felt super stable in my Hoka’s and loved the camel back I got from Free People. We then hit up Moab, only 30 minutes away, for a major dune buggy adventure.
 
That night, Emily braided my hair as she usually does when we are on vacation together. I wish I knew how to french braid my own hair. 

I drank one of the best margaritas I’ve ever had, made s’mores again with dark chocolate bark and passssssed out. 

We hit the road at 10am the next day and walked in our front door by 7p. 

I can’t think of a better place to get off the grid and be with loved ones for a weekend.
#OutsideTogether

Went to see Barbie last night and left in tears! @americaferrera monologue hit me so hard. Leaving it with you cause it’s important:

“It is literally impossible to be a woman. You are so beautiful, and so smart, and it kills me that you don’t think you’re good enough. Like, we have to always be extraordinary, but somehow we’re always doing it wrong.

You have to be thin, but not too thin. And you can never say you want to be thin. You have to say you want to be healthy, but also you have to be thin. You have to have money, but you can’t ask for money because that’s crass. You have to be a boss, but you can’t be mean. You have to lead, but you can’t squash other people’s ideas. You’re supposed to love being a mother, but don’t talk about your kids all the damn time. You have to be a career woman, but also always be looking out for other people. You have to answer for men’s bad behavior, which is insane, but if you point that out, you’re accused of complaining. You’re supposed to stay pretty for men, but not so pretty that you tempt them too much or that you threaten other women because you’re supposed to be a part of the sisterhood. But always stand out and always be grateful. But never forget that the system is rigged. So find a way to acknowledge that but also always be grateful. You have to never get old, never be rude, never show off, never be selfish, never fall down, never fail, never show fear, never get out of line. It’s too hard! It’s too contradictory and nobody gives you a medal or says thank you! And it turns out in fact that not only are you doing everything wrong, but also everything is your fault.

I’m just so tired of watching myself and every single other woman tie herself into knots so that people will like us. And if all of that is also true for a doll just representing women, then I don’t even know”.

Over the past five years, my fertility struggles brought a lot of anxiety into my life. This anxiety continues, and some days it feels never-ending. If I used surrogacy, I thought my chances of having baby #2 would be higher. I'm learning that is not necessarily true. After multiple miscarriages, I made it part of my mission to help inform and raise awareness about fertility issues. I am thrilled to share that I host the new @dearmediastudio podcast #FertilityFM brought to you by @ccrmfertility. On Fertility FM, I continue to share my fertility journey, including my recent surrogacy story. Each week, I will sit down with fellow Dear Media network creators and CCRM doctors who will provide their expertise on IVF, egg freezing, financial planning, nuances of black fertility, LGBTQ family planning, and more. On 10/26, check out the first episode of Fertility FM wherever you get your podcasts!

I got into bed with Sonny on Christmas night and he said ” I feel like I only got one present”. I reminded him he was moving through all the gifts so fast, so intent on this one he REALLY wanted that he didn’t take the time to notice all the awesome things he dashed through. He said, “you’re right Mom, next year I’m gonna slow down”. And I thought, well, perfect. Shouldn’t we all.

I have to be honest. Skiing is not for me. All the shit to carry, the reluctant children, the cold, the masses, the pain… I’m sorry, just no. The pictures are cute, but they are deceiving. There’s obviously amazing moments in between the chaos and fun looks to assemble, but I can’t say it’s worth it. There. I said it.

We probably all know my hair saga by now, right? (I can’t stop talking, thinking and obsessing about it). I chopped it, bleached it, went back caramel-y brown and now I’m just letting it grow, not using any bleach and getting it to a healthier place. Being experimental with hair is fun, but the fun lasts so much shorter than the maintenance. I’ve been taking @wellbel for 2.5 months now and I’m prettyyyyy sure I’m starting to see a difference. But for now, this is how I’ve been wearing my hair pretty much every day.

In: 💋THIS💋
